---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/sections/Navbar.astro';
import MenuDrawer from '../../components/sections/MenuDrawer.astro';
import CityPickerDialog from '../../components/sections/CityPickerDialog.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/sections/Footer.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../components/atoms/Breadcrumb.astro';

const url = Astro.url.toString();
const schemaLD = [
  {
    '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
    itemListElement: [
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://japanauto.ca/' },
      { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Accessibility', item: url },
    ],
  },
  {
    '@type': 'WebPage',
    '@id': `${url}#page`,
    name: 'Accessibility — japanauto.ca',
    description: 'japanauto.ca accessibility commitment and how to report barriers.',
    url,
    inLanguage: 'en-CA',
    publisher: { '@id': 'https://japanauto.ca/#organization' },
  },
];
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Accessibility — japanauto.ca"
  description="japanauto.ca's accessibility commitment: we target WCAG 2.1 AA, treat it as ongoing work, and explain how to report a barrier so we can fix it."
  canonical={url}
  schemaLD={schemaLD}
>
  <Navbar slot="navbar" />
  <MenuDrawer slot="menu-drawer" />
  <CityPickerDialog slot="city-picker" />
  <Footer slot="footer" />

  <Breadcrumb
    items={[
      { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
      { label: 'Accessibility' },
    ]}
  />

  <article class="section" style="padding-top:8px;max-width:720px">
    <h1 class="t-display-l" style="font-size:30px;line-height:38px;margin-bottom:16px">Accessibility</h1>

    <p class="t-body-m" style="font-size:15px;line-height:23px;margin-bottom:14px">
      japanauto.ca is a Canadian marketplace for used Japanese cars and salvage-yard parts, based
      in Calgary, AB, and used by buyers and sellers across Toronto, Montreal, Vancouver, Calgary,
      Edmonton, and Ottawa. We want the site to work for everyone who visits it, including people
      who use screen readers, keyboard navigation, screen magnification, or other assistive
      technology. This page explains what we aim for and how to tell us when something gets in
      your way.
    </p>

    <h2 class="t-h-l" style="font-size:20px;line-height:28px;margin:24px 0 10px">Our target</h2>
    <p class="t-body-m" style="font-size:15px;line-height:23px;margin-bottom:14px">
      We design and build against the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 at Level AA
      as our reference standard. That is the target we hold ourselves to as we add features and
      revise existing pages.
    </p>

    <h2 class="t-h-l" style="font-size:20px;line-height:28px;margin:24px 0 10px">What we do</h2>
    <p class="t-body-m" style="font-size:15px;line-height:23px;margin-bottom:14px">
      In practice, this means we work toward the following on every page:
    </p>
    <ul class="t-body-m" style="font-size:15px;line-height:23px;margin:0 0 14px;padding-left:22px">
      <li style="margin-bottom:8px">Semantic HTML &mdash; headings, landmarks, lists, and buttons marked up for their actual role, so assistive technology can announce the structure correctly.</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom:8px">Full keyboard navigation &mdash; you can reach and operate menus, filters, forms, and listing controls without a mouse, with a visible focus indicator.</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom:8px">Alt text on listing photos, so vehicle and parts images are described rather than skipped.</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom:8px">Colour contrast between text and its background that meets the AA thresholds, and information that never relies on colour alone.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="t-h-l" style="font-size:20px;line-height:28px;margin:24px 0 10px">A work in progress</h2>
    <p class="t-body-m" style="font-size:15px;line-height:23px;margin-bottom:14px">
      Accessibility is ongoing work, not a finished state. We do not claim full conformance with
      WCAG 2.1 AA across the whole site. Some pages, third-party components, and seller-supplied
      content will fall short of our target, and new features can introduce issues we have not yet
      caught. We treat reported barriers as bugs and prioritise them alongside our other work.
    </p>

    <h2 class="t-h-l" style="font-size:20px;line-height:28px;margin:24px 0 10px">Report a barrier</h2>
    <p class="t-body-m" style="font-size:15px;line-height:23px;margin-bottom:14px">
      If any part of japanauto.ca is hard or impossible to use, please tell us. Email
      <a href="mailto:support@japanauto.ca?subject=Accessibility" style="color:var(--color-ink-strong);text-decoration:underline">support@japanauto.ca</a>
      with the page URL, what you were trying to do, and the assistive technology, browser, or
      device you were using if you know it. You can also reach us by phone at
      <a href="tel:+18335272622" style="color:var(--color-ink-strong);text-decoration:underline">1-833-527-2622</a>.
      We aim to acknowledge accessibility reports within a few business days and will work with you
      on the information or transaction you were trying to complete.
    </p>

    <h2 class="t-h-l" style="font-size:20px;line-height:28px;margin:24px 0 10px">Ontario (AODA)</h2>
    <p class="t-body-m" style="font-size:15px;line-height:23px;margin-bottom:14px">
      Because we operate in Ontario, we are aware of the Accessibility for Ontarians with
      Disabilities Act (AODA) and its Integrated Accessibility Standards for information and
      communications. Our WCAG 2.1 AA target and our reporting process are how we work toward
      those expectations. If you need information from this site in an alternative format, contact
      us using the details above and we will do our best to provide it.
    </p>

    <p class="t-body-m ink-muted" style="font-size:13px;line-height:20px;margin-top:24px">
      Effective date: 5 July 2026. We review this statement as the site changes.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
